29 * This file is partially autogenerated, although currently with some manual
30 * fixups afterwards. In future, it should be entirely autogenerated, in order
31 * to ensure that the definitions herein remain in sync with those used by the
32 * GuC's own firmware.
33 *
34 * EDITING THIS FILE IS THEREFORE NOT RECOMMENDED - YOUR CHANGES MAY BE LOST.

48/* Work queue item header definitions */
49#define WQ_STATUS_ACTIVE 1
50#define WQ_STATUS_SUSPENDED 2
51#define WQ_STATUS_CMD_ERROR 3
52#define WQ_STATUS_ENGINE_ID_NOT_USED 4
53#define WQ_STATUS_SUSPENDED_FROM_RESET 5
54#define WQ_TYPE_SHIFT 0
55#define WQ_TYPE_BATCH_BUF (0x1 << WQ_TYPE_SHIFT)
56#define WQ_TYPE_PSEUDO (0x2 << WQ_TYPE_SHIFT)
57#define WQ_TYPE_INORDER (0x3 << WQ_TYPE_SHIFT)
58#define WQ_TARGET_SHIFT 10
59#define WQ_LEN_SHIFT 16
60#define WQ_NO_WCFLUSH_WAIT (1 << 27)
61#define WQ_PRESENT_WORKLOAD (1 << 28)
62#define WQ_WORKLOAD_SHIFT 29
63#define WQ_WORKLOAD_GENERAL (0 << WQ_WORKLOAD_SHIFT)
64#define WQ_WORKLOAD_GPGPU (1 << WQ_WORKLOAD_SHIFT)
65#define WQ_WORKLOAD_TOUCH (2 << WQ_WORKLOAD_SHIFT)
66
67#define WQ_RING_TAIL_SHIFT 20
68#define WQ_RING_TAIL_MASK (0x7FF << WQ_RING_TAIL_SHIFT)

70#define GUC_DOORBELL_ENABLED 1
71#define GUC_DOORBELL_DISABLED 0

73#define GUC_CTX_DESC_ATTR_ACTIVE (1 << 0)

75#define GUC_CTX_DESC_ATTR_KERNEL (1 << 2)
76#define GUC_CTX_DESC_ATTR_PREEMPT (1 << 3)

79#define GUC_CTX_DESC_ATTR_PCH (1 << 6)
80#define GUC_CTX_DESC_ATTR_TERMINATED (1 << 7)

82/* The guc control data is 10 DWORDs */
83#define GUC_CTL_CTXINFO 0

88#define GUC_CTL_DEVICE_INFO 3
89#define GUC_CTL_GTTYPE_SHIFT 0
90#define GUC_CTL_COREFAMILY_SHIFT 7
91#define GUC_CTL_LOG_PARAMS 4
92#define GUC_LOG_VALID (1 << 0)
93#define GUC_LOG_NOTIFY_ON_HALF_FULL (1 << 1)
94#define GUC_LOG_ALLOC_IN_MEGABYTE (1 << 3)
95#define GUC_LOG_CRASH_PAGES 1
96#define GUC_LOG_CRASH_SHIFT 4
97#define GUC_LOG_DPC_PAGES 3
98#define GUC_LOG_DPC_SHIFT 6
99#define GUC_LOG_ISR_PAGES 3
100#define GUC_LOG_ISR_SHIFT 9
101#define GUC_LOG_BUF_ADDR_SHIFT 12
102#define GUC_CTL_PAGE_FAULT_CONTROL 5
103#define GUC_CTL_WA 6
104#define GUC_CTL_WA_UK_BY_DRIVER (1 << 3)
105#define GUC_CTL_FEATURE 7
106#define GUC_CTL_VCS2_ENABLED (1 << 0)
107#define GUC_CTL_KERNEL_SUBMISSIONS (1 << 1)
108#define GUC_CTL_FEATURE2 (1 << 2)
109#define GUC_CTL_POWER_GATING (1 << 3)
110#define GUC_CTL_DISABLE_SCHEDULER (1 << 4)
111#define GUC_CTL_PREEMPTION_LOG (1 << 5)
112#define GUC_CTL_ENABLE_SLPC (1 << 7)
113#define GUC_CTL_RESET_ON_PREMPT_FAILURE (1 << 8)
114#define GUC_CTL_DEBUG 8
115#define GUC_LOG_VERBOSITY_SHIFT 0
116#define GUC_LOG_VERBOSITY_LOW (0 << GUC_LOG_VERBOSITY_SHIFT)
117#define GUC_LOG_VERBOSITY_MED (1 << GUC_LOG_VERBOSITY_SHIFT)
118#define GUC_LOG_VERBOSITY_HIGH (2 << GUC_LOG_VERBOSITY_SHIFT)
119#define GUC_LOG_VERBOSITY_ULTRA (3 << GUC_LOG_VERBOSITY_SHIFT)
120/* Verbosity range-check limits, without the shift */
121#define GUC_LOG_VERBOSITY_MIN 0
122#define GUC_LOG_VERBOSITY_MAX 3
123#define GUC_CTL_RSRVD 9

232/* This Action will be programmed in C180 - SOFT_SCRATCH_O_REG */
233enum host2guc_action {
234 HOST2GUC_ACTION_DEFAULT = 0x0,
235 HOST2GUC_ACTION_SAMPLE_FORCEWAKE = 0x6,
236 HOST2GUC_ACTION_ALLOCATE_DOORBELL = 0x10,
237 HOST2GUC_ACTION_DEALLOCATE_DOORBELL = 0x20,
238 HOST2GUC_ACTION_ENTER_S_STATE = 0x501,
239 HOST2GUC_ACTION_EXIT_S_STATE = 0x502,
240 HOST2GUC_ACTION_SLPC_REQUEST = 0x3003,
241 HOST2GUC_ACTION_LIMIT
242};
243
244/*
245 * The GuC sends its response to a command by overwriting the
246 * command in SS0. The response is distinguishable from a command
247 * by the fact that all the MASK bits are set. The remaining bits
248 * give more detail.
249 */
250#define GUC2HOST_RESPONSE_MASK ((u32)0xF0000000)
251#define GUC2HOST_IS_RESPONSE(x) ((u32)(x) >= GUC2HOST_RESPONSE_MASK)
252#define GUC2HOST_STATUS(x) (GUC2HOST_RESPONSE_MASK | (x))
253
254/* GUC will return status back to SOFT_SCRATCH_O_REG */
255enum guc2host_status {
256 GUC2HOST_STATUS_SUCCESS = GUC2HOST_STATUS(0x0),
257 GUC2HOST_STATUS_ALLOCATE_DOORBELL_FAIL = GUC2HOST_STATUS(0x10),
258 GUC2HOST_STATUS_DEALLOCATE_DOORBELL_FAIL = GUC2HOST_STATUS(0x20),
259 GUC2HOST_STATUS_GENERIC_FAIL = GUC2HOST_STATUS(0x0000F000)
260};
